
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-miers-tls-sas-00.txt'>
    <title>"Short Authentication Strings for TLS", Ian Miers, Matthew Green, Eric Rescorla</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-miers-tls-sas-00.txt</link>
    <description>TLS and DTLS connections generally rely on a PKI, a shared secret, or endpoint fingerprints for endpoint authentication.  This document describes an authentication mechanism which instead generates a "short authentication string" (SAS) as an emergent property of the connection.  The SAS can then be verified via an external channel in order to authenticate the connection.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-02-14T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
